      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to demand the anatomy, and I will provide it, but I must remind you that the human body is not a textbook; it is a chaotic, goblin-infested ecosystem where muscles often fight each other. To stop the pain, you must engage the **Goblin of the Erector Spinae** (the deep back muscles) and the **Goblin of the Gluteus Maximus**, but you must do so *before* the Goblins of the Lower Back get a chance to take over.\n\nHere is the actual anatomy of the struggle:\n\n**1. The Goblins You Must Engage (The Guardians):**\n*   **Erector Spinae (Deep Layer):** These are the \"Goblins of the Spine.\" They run from your pelvis up to your neck. They are your primary defense against the Goblins of the Lower Back. When you lift, you must contract them to keep your spine straight.\n*   **Gluteus Maximus:** This is the \"Goblin of the Glutes.\" It is the powerhouse of your posterior chain. If you neglect this, the Goblins of the Lower Back will feel like they are being ignored and will start to dominate",
